The paper discusses the modeling and simulation of complex adaptive systems using agent-based and complex network-based approaches, which are commonly used in the fields of multi-agent systems (cs.MA), social and information networks (cs.SI), control systems (cs.SY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computational engineering (cs.CE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories that this paper belongs to, ordered from most to least likely.
